Resamples a tensor.

Source: R/resampleTensorUtilities.R
resampleTensorLike.Rd

Resamples a tensor based on the reference tensor and interpolation type.

resampleTensorLike(
  inputTensor,
  referenceTensor,
  interpolationType = "nearestNeighbor"
)

Arguments

inputTensor

tensor to be resampled.
referenceTensor

Reference tensor of rank 4 or 5 (for 2-D or 3-D volumes, respectively).
interpolationType

type of interpolation for resampling. Can be nearestNeighbor, linear, or cubic.

Value

a tensor

Examples


library( keras )

K <- keras::backend()

inputTensor <- K$ones( c( 2L, 10L, 10L, 10L, 3L ) )
referenceTensor <- K$ones( c( 2L, 12L, 13L, 14L, 3L ) )

outputTensor <- resampleTensorLike( inputTensor, referenceTensor )
